  (871, 'Can you upgrade my commercial electrical system while keeping my business operational?', 'Absolutely. We specialize in phased upgrades and can often work during off-hours or coordinate schedules that minimize disruption to your Pacific Palisades operations. Our team plans carefully to maintain power availability throughout installation, coordinate all permits, and communicate every step of the process. You keep your business running smoothly while we handle the technical work efficiently and to code.', 2),

  (871, 'Does Shaffer Construction help with energy rebates and incentive paperwork?', 'Yes—that''s part of our service. California utilities and state programs offer substantial rebates for commercial energy efficiency projects, and we navigate the application process for our Pacific Palisades clients. We handle all documentation, energy calculations, and submissions so you can focus on running your business. Many clients see significant portions of their upgrade costs covered through available incentive programs.', 3),

  (871, 'How long does a typical commercial energy efficiency project take in Pacific Palisades?', 'Project timelines vary based on scope: a lighting retrofit might take 1-2 weeks, while comprehensive building automation could take 4-8 weeks. Shaffer Construction schedules work strategically around your business hours and ensures every phase is completed efficiently and to code. We''ll provide a detailed timeline upfront and keep you updated throughout the entire project.', 4),

  (871, 'What''s involved in a commercial energy audit for Pacific Palisades businesses?', 'Our energy audit analyzes your current systems—lighting, HVAC, electrical distribution, controls, and more—to identify inefficiencies and potential improvements. We provide a detailed report with cost-benefit analysis for each recommendation, prioritized by impact and ROI. This helps you make informed decisions about which upgrades to pursue first and ensures your investment delivers measurable results.', 5);

